        map -&gt; map.get(true) == 0 || map.get(false) == 0
    ));
```

# One stream - Custom Collector

If we generalize the task, it can be tackled using a *custom collector*, which makes uses a boolean array as the accumulation type (similar approaches you can in implementation&#39;s of built-in collectors from the `Collectors` class).

To create a *custom collector*, we can make use of the static method [`Collector.of()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Collector.html).

